</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="299" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1617]" pageId="6" pageNumber="299">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1555,1581]" pageId="6" pageNumber="299">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is derived from Latin 
<emphasis box="[727,842,1555,1580]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="299">pectinatus</emphasis>
, referring to the basal 2/3 of the male antenna flagellumis pectinated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
